race.description: Hahn Super Dry Country Boosted Handciap
race.comment: DOUBTFREE (10) dropped back in trip last start at Albury where he was well beaten in this grade in a disappointing performance first-up for the new stable. Suspect McDougall will take the bull by the horns today as that's how he has performed best in recent races. Prior form stacks up and he can return to winning ways today. HELLINDA (2) stepped up to Highway grade last start following a BM66 win at Bathurst two starts ago. He drops right back to a 58 today and the claim of Cole comes in handy. Maps well and can bounce back to form. TALUK (3) bounced back at Corowa when chasing a smart one over 1000m. Suspect she'll be better out to this trip again today and she rates well off that latest effort. BURROWA (4) can resume on a positive note after ending last campaign with back-to-back wins.
